author: Kelly Terez
title: Michigan State Wins After Michigan Drops Punt Snap
text:
Share Article 
Rey Del Rio/Getty Images (ANN ARBOR, Mich.) -- It ain't over 'til it's over. 
During a Michigan and Michigan State game on Saturday, the Wolverines were leading 23-10 with 10 seconds left on the clock. 
Michigan's punter Blake O'Neill fumbled a punt snap which Michigan State recovered, with Jalen Watts-Jackson taking the ball to the endzone to make a touchdown just as the clock ran out. 
"That's why football is loved so much in America," Michigan State coach Mark Dantonio said. "It's because things like this happen. Every now and then, they happen."
